{"sectionId":713,"sectionIdLiteral":"713","humanId":"lesson-294","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"My body is a wholly neutral thing.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 294"},"annotation":"W-294","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-294\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"713#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I am a Son of God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>And can I be another thing as well?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Did God create the mortal and corruptible?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>What use has God‚Äôs beloved Son for what must die?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>And yet a neutral thing does not see death, for thoughts of fear are not invested there, nor is a mockery of love bestowed upon it.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Its neutrality protects it while it has a use.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>And afterwards, without a purpose, it is laid aside.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>It is not sick nor old nor hurt.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>It is but functionless, unneeded and cast off.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#1:10\"><span class=\"snr\">10</span>Let me not see it more than this today; of service for a while and fit to serve, to keep its usefulness while it can serve, and then to be replaced for greater good.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"713#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>My body, Father, cannot be Your Son.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>And what is not created cannot be sinful nor sinless; neither good nor bad.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"713#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me, then, use this dream to help Your plan that we awaken from all dreams we made.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"I am a Son of God. And can I be another thing as well? Did God create the mortal and corruptible? What use has God‚Äôs beloved Son for what must die? And yet a neutral thing does not see death, for","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 294: My body is a wholly neutral thing | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†294 ‚ÄúMy body is a wholly neutral thing‚Äù: I am a Son of God. And can I be another thing as well? Did God create the mortal‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"8. What Is the Real World?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":709,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-real-world"]}},{"label":"Lesson 294","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":713,"slugs":["lesson-294","my-body-is-a-wholly-neutral-thing"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"8. What Is the Real World?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":709,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-real-world"]}},{"label":"Lesson 294","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":713,"slugs":["lesson-294","my-body-is-a-wholly-neutral-thing"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionI